content:
Nice clash, but the statement doesn't currently match the solution, since it never states that you can't re-use digits.

Without mentioning that there is no reason that any test case should give "No codes" since even if the only available digits are "5" and "6" like with Test 3, you could still make codes like "556", "665", etc. There would also be more answers for all other tests too.

Best to correct the statement to match the solution.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: This is pretty clear and not very hard. Maybe a little bit long for short mode but okay for long mode

All sections

Goal

Output

* Please format "No codes" as a {{constant}} and remove the quotation marks.

Cases
* Please revise the 1st, 2nd and 4th pairs of cases so that each pair is similar but does not require the same answer.

Stub generator

Thanks.
